race.comment: SINATRA (8) looks to have more upside than most of these after being heavily supported on debut when a fighting second over 1410m at this track. Has further improvement to come and drawn to get the gun run. Leading player. SO SAIN (10) found form at her last three runs and went under narrowly in the heavy going when second over 1420m at Grafton. Deep into the prep and shapes as the main danger. STAR CHEVAL (11) went back early from the wide draw when resuming with a battling fifth over 1200m at Murwillumbah. Looking for the extra ground now and can take a hand in the finish. TARAVIA (6) returns from a lay-off. Placed in a recent trial at the Gold Coast. Might need the run but respect any market confidence.
